50|$|The Handle System is {{compatible}} with the <b>Domain</b> <b>Name</b> System (DNS), but does not require it, unlike persistent identifiers such as PURLs or ARKs, which are similar to handles, but which utilise <b>domain</b> <b>names.</b> However, unlike these domain-name based approaches, handles do require a separate prefix registration process and handle servers separate from the <b>domain</b> <b>name</b> <b>servers.</b>|$|R
